The paper discusses methods for learning vector representations of SQL queries to support workload analytics tasks, which are typically studied in the database (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL) communities. The paper also evaluates the performance of these methods on synthetic and real SQL workloads, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
